The paper discusses the use of a deep generative model for replicating the behavior of an active appearance model (AAM) in generating face stimuli. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks and variational auto-encoders, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the learning of latent variables and the capture of shape knowledge, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of neural responses to face stimuli, which is a topic in natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
